title.narrative: 205 GENERATE DEMAND FOR POSITIVE PRACTICES IN NUTRITION

description.narrative: By 2022, government and partners have enhanced capacities to generate demand for positive practices that improve the nutritional status of children, adolescents and women, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluations, Research And Data, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

title.narrative: By 2022, government and partners have enhanced capacities to generate demand for positive practices that improve the nutritionalstatus of children, adolescents and women

description.narrative: Capacity of government, partners and civil society was enhanced on social behaviour change communication (SBCC) for uptake of nutrition services during COVID through evidence based SBCC plans of action to support POSHAN Abhiyan, Jan Andolan and Anaemia Mukt Bharat across 14 states. Jan Andolan Dashboard supported during Poshan Maah and Poshan Pakhwada reporting over 200,000,000 community events. Strategic messages on Nutrition were integrated as part of outreach community engagement programmes around COVID-prevention. State specific SBCC initiatives like Yuvodaya in Chhattisgarh, Hello Didi in Uttar Pradesh, Artists Federation in Odisha ensured improved reach of nutrition messages using digital mediums edutainment formats. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/01/2022
